race.comment: INDENTATIONS (4) is progressing well with another good run last time, placing (24.95) from Box 5 at this track. One of the contenders. BOSS BANDIT (2) was strongly fancied to break through last time and justified the confidence with a maiden win at this track over 440m (25.18). Nicely drawn here. Has two placings this course. Rates a leading chance again. GENERAL LEE (6) goes very well at this journey here having never missed the frame including two wins and two placings. Placed last time (21.20) at Nowra in a Grade 5, finishing second and beaten 0.8 lengths. Makes strong appeal on best. NIETA ROSE (1) must be respected despite an unplaced effort here most recently.
